00:24:50.570 --> 00:24:53.670
Rasada eventually submitted
to Yohannes and was reinstated

00:24:53.670 --> 00:24:55.910
as ruler of Gojjam and Darmut.

00:24:55.910 --> 00:24:57.990
He continued to be a loyal vessel

00:24:57.990 --> 00:25:01.150
until the empower dynamic shifted
again with the reckoning presence

00:25:01.150 --> 00:25:03.180
of Menilek Shoa who success

00:25:03.180 --> 00:25:06.730
in [Inaudible] signaled a
potentially powerful rival

00:25:06.730 --> 00:25:08.140
to the throne.

00:25:08.140 --> 00:25:09.940
Emperor Yohannes was preoccupied

00:25:09.940 --> 00:25:14.180
with the impending Egyptian
menace immediately continued

00:25:14.180 --> 00:25:17.100
to advance [Inaudible] the base
that he had founded in [Inaudible]

00:25:17.100 --> 00:25:20.100
through [Inaudible]
en route to Ghana.

00:25:20.100 --> 00:25:22.570
The clergy intervened to
divert the confrontation

00:25:22.570 --> 00:25:24.020
between Yohannes and Menilek.

00:25:24.020 --> 00:25:28.450 position:56%
In 1878 Menilek carried the
traditional Stone of Penitence asked

00:25:28.450 --> 00:25:32.370
for forgiveness and swore his
allegiance to Emperor Yohannes.

00:25:32.370 --> 00:25:35.390
Emperor Yohannes effort to
maintain a balance of military

00:25:35.390 --> 00:25:38.500
and political power between
Menilek and [Inaudible] interfered

00:25:38.500 --> 00:25:41.440
with Menilek's thinly
veiled imperial design.

00:25:41.440 --> 00:25:45.120
The emperor increasingly favored
Adal, possibly drawing him

00:25:45.120 --> 00:25:47.560
into the family with the
marriage of Yohannes's nephew

00:25:47.560 --> 00:25:52.070 position:56%
to Adal's daughter in November 1879.

00:25:52.070 --> 00:25:55.110
Adal was appointed
[Inaudible] of Gojjam and Kafah

00:25:55.110 --> 00:26:00.650
in January 1880 bringing his
status to par with Menilek.

00:26:00.650 --> 00:26:03.660
Menilek continued to
challenge [Inaudible] authority

00:26:03.660 --> 00:26:06.320
and territorial holdings
defeating him

00:26:06.320 --> 00:26:10.220
at the Battle of Babu in May 1882.

00:26:10.220 --> 00:26:11.840
Angered by the unrest caused

00:26:11.840 --> 00:26:15.380
by these rivalries Yohannes
summoned Menilek and [Inaudible]

00:26:15.380 --> 00:26:18.570
to chide them for their actions

00:26:18.570 --> 00:26:21.150
and redefined their
spheres of influence.

00:26:21.150 --> 00:26:23.860
He redistributed their land
holdings taking [Inaudible]

00:26:23.860 --> 00:26:26.960
from Gojjam and Weloa from Shoa.

00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:30.060
Menilek was instructed to give
up all the arms he had secured

00:26:30.060 --> 00:26:33.830
from the battle to [Inaudible] the
trusted general of the Emperor.

00:26:33.830 --> 00:26:38.230
Yohannes pardoned [Inaudible] and
returned all his confiscated arms.

00:26:38.230 --> 00:26:41.840
Both the military and political
terms this agreement dealt a severe

00:26:41.840 --> 00:26:43.270
blow to Menilek.

00:26:43.270 --> 00:26:46.310
The administration of [Inaudible]
is divided into two and given

00:26:46.310 --> 00:26:50.830
to [Inaudible] and to the
emperor's young son [Inaudible].

00:26:50.830 --> 00:26:53.370
This is critical to
pay attention to.

00:26:53.370 --> 00:26:56.840
At this critical juncture
Yohannes proposed the marriage

00:26:56.840 --> 00:27:02.380
of the same son [Inaudible]
to Menilek's daughter.

00:27:02.380 --> 00:27:06.230
Accounts agree that the
proposal may have been initiated

00:27:06.230 --> 00:27:10.170
by Emperor Yohannes with
several factors in mind.

00:27:10.170 --> 00:27:13.190 position:56%
Such a marriage would soften the
slight of [Inaudible] made decisions

00:27:13.190 --> 00:27:16.580
on Menilek's pride
indicating his respectability

00:27:16.580 --> 00:27:18.850
as a partner in power.

00:27:18.850 --> 00:27:20.840
Secession may also
have been an issue.

00:27:20.840 --> 00:27:24.440 position:56%
Menilek did not have a male heir
and Yohannes may have wanted Menilek

00:27:24.440 --> 00:27:29.790
to acknowledge his son
[Inaudible] as heir.

00:27:29.790 --> 00:27:36.210
Menilek's official chronicler
[Inaudible] writes that Menilek --

00:27:36.210 --> 00:27:37.660
that Yohannes was displeased

00:27:37.660 --> 00:27:39.980
with Menilek's actions
[Inaudible] implying

00:27:39.980 --> 00:27:44.320
that such a connection would have
kept the King in close proximity,

00:27:44.320 --> 00:27:48.890
so to keep an eye on Menilek may
have been another speculation.

00:27:48.890 --> 00:27:51.320
Each speculation holds
some truth and point

00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:52.850
to Menilek's growing importance

00:27:52.850 --> 00:27:56.030
as the impending successor
to imperial authority.

00:27:56.030 --> 00:28:00.090
And the underlying significance
of the dynastic alliance.

00:28:00.090 --> 00:28:02.850
So this marriage takes place.

00:28:02.850 --> 00:28:07.470
Historians hint that the young
age of Zawditu to Araya Selassie

00:28:07.470 --> 00:28:11.290
around six and 13 years old
respectively and the death

00:28:11.290 --> 00:28:15.200
of Araya Selassie five years
later made their marriage an event

00:28:15.200 --> 00:28:18.610
of symbolic union rather
than a practical one.

00:28:18.610 --> 00:28:22.090
Ras Araya Selassie is the one
sitting next to his father

00:28:22.090 --> 00:28:24.290
to the right of his father.

00:28:24.290 --> 00:28:27.920 position:56%
Despite his youth Ras Araya Selassie
had been entrusted with the command

00:28:27.920 --> 00:28:32.900
of [Inaudible] with
[Inaudible] as deputy in 1883.

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:36.710
He was later transferred
to [Inaudible] in 1886

00:28:36.710 --> 00:28:38.380
and he remained an
administrator even

00:28:38.380 --> 00:28:41.570
at that young age,
there for two years.

00:28:41.570 --> 00:28:43.880
So it's obvious as Ras
Araya Selassie tells us

